# Color Legends for Visual Indicators

When using colored UI elements (borders, badges, status indicators), **always provide a legend** explaining what the colors mean. Users should never have to guess what a color represents.

## When to Use Legends

Add a legend when you have:
- Cards with colored left borders (`border-l-4 border-l-green-500`)
- Status badges with different colors
- Color-coded categories or states
- Any UI where color conveys meaning

## Legend Pattern

Use this consistent pattern across the app:

```tsx
interface StatusItem {
    label: string
    color: string  // Tailwind class like "bg-emerald-500"
    icon: typeof LucideIcon
}

const STATUS_ITEMS: StatusItem[] = [
    { label: "Verified", color: "bg-emerald-500", icon: CheckCircle2 },
    { label: "Pending", color: "bg-slate-300", icon: Clock },
]

export function StatusLegend({ className }: { className?: string }) {
    return (
        <div className={cn("flex items-center gap-6 text-sm", className)}>
            <span className="text-muted-foreground font-medium">Status:</span>
            {STATUS_ITEMS.map((item) => {
                const Icon = item.icon
                return (
                    <div key={item.label} className="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <div className={cn("h-2 w-10 rounded-full", item.color)} />
                        <Icon className="h-3.5 w-3.5 text-muted-foreground" />
                        <span className="text-foreground font-medium">{item.label}</span>
                    </div>
                )
            })}
        </div>
    )
}
```

## Placement

Place legends:
- **Below page headers**, before main content
- **Above filterable content** (before tabs/filters)
- **Only when relevant content is visible** (conditional rendering)

## Examples

✅ **Advisory page**: Status legend shows Verified/Endorsed/Awaiting Review
✅ **Today page**: Action items legend shows Decisions/Blockers/Mentions  
✅ **Org Blueprint**: Coverage legend shows Covered/Partial/Gap

❌ **Don't**: Use colored borders without explanation
❌ **Don't**: Put legend at bottom or in tooltips only
❌ **Don't**: Create inconsistent legend styles across pages
